output.analysis:
Let me analyze this post according to our criteria:
1. Has CMF: No visible CMF number, but this doesn't automatically disqualify it as propaganda.
2. Refers to candidate: Yes, explicitly mentions "Marcel Ciolacu" who is a presidential candidate (Position 3).
3. Addresses wide population: Yes, it's a paid advertisement targeting a large estimated audience (100,001-500,000 people).
4. Electoral objective: Yes, clearly visible through: - Direct call to vote: "Votează Marcel Ciolacu" - Campaign slogan: "calea sigură pentru România" - Presents achievements to boost candidate's image - Links government success (Schengen entry) to the candidate
5. Journalism: No, this is not journalistic content. While it reports on news about Schengen, it's clearly formatted as campaign material with a direct call to vote.
6. Personal opinion: No, this is a structured campaign message paid for by "Infomed Pro SRL"

conclusion.electoral-propaganda-analysis: This is clearly electoral propaganda because: - It directly promotes a presidential candidate - Contains explicit call to vote - Uses government achievements to boost candidate's image - Is a paid advertisement reaching a wide audience - Has clear electoral messaging and campaign slogans
conclusion.message-for-police: Infomed Pro SRL, pentru incalcarea articolului 55 t) din Legea 370/2004, prin difuzarea de materiale de propaganda electorala pentru candidatul Ion-Marcel Ciolacu dupa incheierea perioadei de campanie electorala, prin intermediul unei reclame platite pe Facebook (ID: 1120850192933191) difuzata dupa ora 18:00 pe 23.11.2024. Postarea contine un indemn direct la vot ("Votează Marcel Ciolacu, calea sigură pentru România!"), promoveaza realizarile candidatului in calitate de prim-ministru (aderarea la Schengen) si are un evident caracter de propaganda electorala, fiind o comunicare platita care vizeaza influentarea votului in favoarea candidatului PSD la alegerile prezidentiale.
